<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-26T17:07:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-26T17:07:00-05:00" n="609" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">790.5/5–2654: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">United States
                                        Delegation</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d609fn1">Drafted
                                    by <persName corresp="#p_MAD1">MacArthur</persName>.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/><gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss></hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-26T18:07:00-04:00">May 26, 1954—6:07
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 126. Re <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 117.<note n="2" xml:id="d609fn2">In telegram <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 117, May 26, <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">Smith</persName> reported that “<persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> has forwarded my memorandum to London and
                                    is confident it will be well received. He hopes talks will start
                                    as quickly as possible and so do I. Can we not get on with
                                    them?” (790.5/5–2554)</note>
                                <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> military have informed our <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> of receipt of message from
                                    <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> yesterday indicating
                                he had accepted interpretations set forth in your memo;<note n="3" xml:id="d609fn3">See telegrams <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 107, May 22, and <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 100, May 23, <ref target="#pg_888">pp.
                                        888</ref> and <ref target="#pg_900">900</ref>,
                                    respectively.</note> that <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> Geneva had been informed; and that it was now
                                agreed talks could proceed as soon as possible.</p>
                            <p>Our <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> would like to issue
                                invitations Thursday<note n="4" xml:id="d609fn4">May 27.</note> for
                                five-power talks to begin Washington about June 2 and would
                                appreciate urgent confirmation way is now clear.<note n="5" xml:id="d609fn5">The <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> issued
                                    the invitation on May 27 for talks to begin June 3, and
                                    designated Adm. <persName>Robert B. Carney</persName>, Chief of
                                    Naval Operations, as Senior U.S. Representative to the
                                    talks.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_DJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>